cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT

This paper presents a neural rendering framework that maps a voxelized scene into a high-quality image. The paper focuses on the computer graphics and computer vision aspects of the problem, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a controllable rendering approach, which involves modifying the input geometry and appearance, indicating that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks to achieve its results, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with rendering objects from real images, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
